The high-frequency-response efficiency of tunnel diodes is equivalent to the impedance matching efficiency, ηc, between the diode and antenna11. ηc is defined by calculating the effective power in the diode part assuming an equivalent circuit as shown in Fig. 1, and it is expressed by Eq. (1).1ηc=4RARD(RA+RD)21+ω2CD2(RARDRA+RD)2,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
